items.name: Rate RES1N - SIngle Phase Net Meter
items.description:
This rate is required for all single-phase net-metered accounts above 10 kVA. This rate is subject to prior approval from the Cooperative. Members on this rate shall take both electric distribution and energy services from EnerStar. The installation of motors requiring in excess of 260 amperes starting current shall also be subject to prior approval of the Cooperative.

The settlement shall occur annually on March 31st. If member produces more electricity than consumed, EnerStar will reimburse member at EnerStar's avoided cost. Avoided cost shall be determined by the cost of EnerStar's wholesale power rates charged by Wabash Valley Power Association at the date of settlement. If the net amount of electricity exceeds what member produces within a billing cycle, member will be billed based on this rate schedule.
